Interface Stack

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ImprovedStack
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractStack, ImprovedStackImpl, StackImpl

    public interface Stack
    An implementation of a stack, a data structure of type LIFO (Last In, First Out). Classes implementing this interface must use a List as the underlying data structure to store the elements on the stack. Not all operations on a stack will always be successful. For example, a programmer may try to pop an element from an empty stack. Since we hace not covered exceptions yet, we need another mechanism to report errors. In order to do that, methods of this list will return a ReturnObject that will contain either an object or an error value of the right kind (as defined in ErrorMessage).
